General Motors to Recall 2011 Chevrolet Cruze for Inspections

-- B y   G r e g   C h a n g
-- 
2011-05-04T21:58:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-04/general-motors-to-recall-2011-chevrolet-cruze-for-inspections.html
General Motors said it will recall the
2011 Chevrolet Cruze to inspect for proper installation of the
steering shaft and the automatic transmission shift linkage.  The inspection covers 154,112 Cruze models built in
Lordstown,  Ohio , and sold in the U.S. and Canada. There are
120,295 vehicles in that group with an automatic transmission
that will be inspected for proper installation of the
transmission shift linkage, according to an e-mailed statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Greg Chang at 
 gchang1@bloomberg.net  